# Amazon Future Engineer proudly supports your classroom 

As a Code.org classroom supported by Amazon Future Engineer, **you’re invited to sign-up to receive free additional benefits** such as posters, a free CSTA+ membership, internship and scholarship opportunities, and access to in-depth computer science teaching and student resources.
 
[Amazon Future Engineer (AFE)](https://www.amazonfutureengineer.com/) is a four-part, childhood-to-career program aimed at inspiring and educating students from underrepresented and underserved communities to try computer science and coding. This program provides robust resources tailored to students in grades K-12, and teachers as well. 
 
AFE has partnered with Code.org to offer these resources and benefits to you and your students at no cost and without having to join a waitlist! 

