## Extended Learning on Cloud Computing with AWS Educate
AWS Educate provides students with comprehensive resources for building skills in cloud technology. With a focus on real-world, applied learning experiences, AWS Educate offers young learners access to self-paced cloud computing content designed to introduce cloud computing technologies that drive innovation in fields such as artificial intelligence, voice and facial recognition, gaming, medical advancements, and more.
 
Students 14 or older can join AWS Educate at no cost to get started and receive up to $75 in AWS Promotional Credits to support their AWS Educate learning.
 
##  Scholarship and Internship Opportunities
In partnership with Scholarship America, Amazon Future Engineer provides 100 students from underrepresented and underserved communities with $10,000/year scholarships. These prestigious 4-year scholarships are specifically focused on students pursuing a computer science degree.
 
Scholarship recipients are also offered a guaranteed, paid internship at Amazon after their first year of college. This opportunity supports college students early in their career path while also giving them the chance to apply their CS skills in a practical setting. Interns are partnered with a technical mentor and manager, as well as other interns, to innovate and create new features and services on behalf of Amazon customers.

